intro: Fagara alata, commonly known as the winged soursop, is a tropical plant native to Central and South America. It is a member of the Annonaceae family and is characterized by its distinctive, winged leaves that give it its common name. The plant produces large, spiny fruits that are typically harvested when fully mature. Its foliage is often used in traditional medicine for its purported health benefits. The plant thrives in humid, shaded environments and is often found in rainforest understories.
